[normal]4.5
[normal]              
[normal]However events over the last few years in the US have shown that low
[normal]er
[normal] gas prices on a continental scale can lead to a shift away from high CO
[normal]2 
[normal]coal fired generation to lower emission gas fired generation with a net benefit in total CO
[normal]2
[normal] output.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.6
[normal]              
[normal]Given the presence of prospective shale gas plays being identified on every inhabited continent a simple extrapolation of the US example would suggest that global development of shale gas
[normal],
[normal] in conjunction with renewables and nuclear energy
[normal],
[normal] would displace coal fired power generation and lead to significant reductions in global greenhouse gas emissions over the coming decades.  
