[normal]7.0[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]T[bold]he role of the Wales Office and the Welsh Government in developing a policy framework for the exploration of shale gas.[bold]&#xa0;[bold]7.1
[normal]              
[normal]The onshore hydrocarbon industry welcomes strong
[normal], consistent and evidence 
[normal]based
[normal] regulation policed by 
[normal]a strong regulator
[normal](s)
[normal] with defined 
[normal]terms of reference
[normal].
[normal]  A clear demarcation between surface
[normal] planning
[normal] and sub-surface regulatory regimes and removal of unnecessary burden in terms of cost and 
[normal]human 
[normal]resources 
[normal]for both regulator(s) and operator through overlapping regulation should be a priority of any government.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]7.2
[normal]              
[normal]Any new policy framework should aim to encourage early exploration activities
[normal] through the removal unnecessary regulatory burdens, provision of clear and consistent guidance and encouraging investment by ensuring a stable fiscal regime during the development of this industry.  
